From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: experintellia <280144245+experintellia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 6 Jul 2026 22:34:43 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 5/7] wasm: IMAP/SMTP through a WebSocket-TCP proxy

Browsers cannot open TCP sockets, so on wasm32 connect_tcp_inner tunnels
through a local WS proxy (src/net/ws_tcp.rs): ws_stream_wasm -> duplex
bridge -> SessionStream. TLS still terminates inside wasm, the proxy only
sees ciphertext. DNS resolves via the proxy's /dns/{host} endpoint.
Adds wasm deps: ws_stream_wasm, tokio-util/compat, wasm-bindgen-futures,
plus chrono wasmbind and pgp wasm feature (JS clock instead of
SystemTime::now which panics on wasm32-unknown-unknown).
